{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Due to the richness of natural language, description-based identifiers have high readability and flexibility.",
    "For hybrid identifiers, considering collaborative and textual information of users or items, LLMs can perceive both token-based and description-based identifiers [66,76].",
    "Current work using hybrid identifiers can be divided into different types.",
    "Some of them add item sequence with textual description and ID information respectively into different positions of prompts [179], while others combine token-based and description-based embeddings together for each item in sequences through concatenation [66].• Grounding to candidate items.",
    "After constructing candidate items for recommendation, how to ground the output of LLMs into recommendation item lists is a crucial problem."
  ],
